      "side": 1,
      "message": "Taking this by l-value and then constructing a (malloc\u0027d) temporary into seems odd.\n\nThe data flow here is:\n1. malloc from a non owning view refManifestDataRaw\n2. make two non-owning views of the malloc\u0027d and copy\u0027d data\n3. malloc again for each\n4. deep copy that malloc\u0027d version into another malloc\u0027d version inside of ReferenceManifestData.\n\nWhy not\n```\nif (reference_manifest.length \u003c 2)\n{\n    return std::nullopt;\n}\n\nstd::span\u003cuint8_t\u003e byteView \u003d {reference_manifest_data.ptr, reference_manifest_data.length};\nconst uint8_t length \u003d byteView[1];\nif (length \u003e reference_manifest_data.length) { /* freak out */ }\n\nstd::span\u003cuint8_t\u003e vendorID \u003d byteView.subspan(2, length);\nstd::span\u003cuint8_t\u003e data \u003d byteView.subspan(2 + length, reference_manifest_data.length - 2 - length);\n\nreturn ReferenceManifestData {byteView[0], vendorID, data};\n```\n\nand then change ReferenceManifestData to take random access iterators to uint8_t like data.",
